TY  - JOUR
T1  - Addendum to Stankard and Gupta's Note on Lot Size Scheduling
AU  - Hodgson, Thom J.
Y1  - 1970/03/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.16.7.514
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.16.7.514
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 514
EP  - 517
VL  - 16
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper presents a grouping procedure which yields improved solutions to Bomberger's Lot Size Scheduling Problem [1]. The group definition is a generalization of the group definition proposed by Stankard and Gupta [3]. Moreover, the generalization leads to a pseudo dynamic programming procedure which is readily programmable. Computational experience has shown the procedure to be extremely efficient.
AB  - This paper presents a grouping procedure which yields improved solutions to Bomberger's Lot Size Scheduling Problem [1]. The group definition is a generalization of the group definition proposed by Stankard and Gupta [3]. Moreover, the generalization leads to a pseudo dynamic programming procedure which is readily programmable. Computational experience has shown the procedure to be extremely efficient.
